</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC954628CFEFE19859CE8" author="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 166" refId="ref1984" refString="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E. (1971) The classification, evolution, and dispersal of the winter stonefly genus Allocapnia. Illinois Biological Monographs, 45, 1 - 166." type="journal article" year="1971">Ross &amp; Ricker 1971</bibRefCitation>
), which includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954643BFED61B7F9CE8" authority="Ricker" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1952" box="[636,858,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loshada">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954643BFED61ADB9CEB" box="[636,766,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. loshada</emphasis>
Ricker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954652CFED61C629CE8" authority="Ross" authorityName="Ross" authorityYear="1964" box="[875,1095,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malverna">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954652CFED61BDB9CEB" box="[875,1022,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. malverna</emphasis>
Ross
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546210FED6197D9CC0" authority="Ross &amp; Ricker" authorityName="Ross &amp; Ricker" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mohri">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546210FED61CE69CEB" box="[1111,1219,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. mohri</emphasis>
Ross &amp; Ricker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546722FE2E1A9D9CC0" authority="Ross &amp; Ricker" authorityName="Ross &amp; Ricker" authorityYear="1971" box="[357,696,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polemistis">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546722FE2E19DB9CC3" box="[357,510,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. polemistis</emphasis>
Ross &amp; Ricker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546483FE2E1B049CC3" baseAuthorityName="Claassen" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[708,801,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recta">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546483FE2E1B049CC3" box="[708,801,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. recta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546576FE2E1CD19CC0" authority="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2000" box="[817,1268,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sequatchie">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546576FE2E1BF59CC3" box="[817,976,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sequatchie</emphasis>
Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954674FFE061AAB9CB8" authority="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner." authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner." box="[264,654,444,470]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="starki">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954674FFE06194F9CBB" box="[264,362,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. starki</emphasis>
Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner.
</taxonomicName>
Morphological characteristics used to define the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546288FE061D0E9CBB" baseAuthorityName="Claassen" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1231,1323,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recta">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546288FE061D0E9CBB" box="[1231,1323,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. recta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, as “…dorsal process of the male eighth tergite arcuate or only slightly incised, and situated on a marked posterior elevation of the tergite. The male seventh tergite lacks a process…” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC95467DCFD8E1AB69F20" author="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E." box="[411,659,564,590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 166" refId="ref1984" refString="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E. (1971) The classification, evolution, and dispersal of the winter stonefly genus Allocapnia. Illinois Biological Monographs, 45, 1 - 166." type="journal article" year="1971">Ross &amp; Ricker 1971</bibRefCitation>
), are exhibited by 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546536FD8E1BEF9F23" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[881,970,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546536FD8E1BEF9F23" box="[881,970,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546234FD8E1CE89F23" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[1139,1229,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546234FD8E1CE89F23" box="[1139,1229,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546739FDE619D99F1B" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1952" box="[382,508,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loshada">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546739FDE619D99F1B" box="[382,508,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. loshada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546473FDE61AF79F1B" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2000" box="[564,722,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sequatchie">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546473FDE61AF79F1B" box="[564,722,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sequatchie</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the expanded apical segment of the epiproct dorsal limb and the posteriorly­incised tubercle of the 8 
<superScript id="7C089BBE472EC95465DDFD3E1B829FFC" attach="left" box="[922,935,644,658]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite. However, the lack of a subapical notch on the epiproct limb of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546518FD151B9C9FA6" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[863,953,687,712]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546518FD151B9C9FA6" box="[863,953,687,712]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
easily distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546356FD1519409F9E" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loshada">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546356FD1519409F9E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. loshada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13462A73472EC9546732FD6D199E9F9F" box="[373,443,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[264,367,1389,1413]" captionTargetBox="[327,1254,632,1376]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[312,1285,629,1382]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1A–D. Allocapnia sano sp. nov. A. Male terminalia, lateral. B. Male terminalia, dorsal, SEM micrograph, 200X. C. Male terminalia, dorsal, SEM micrograph, 500X; D. Female terminalia, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2646321/files/figure.svg" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC954678DFD6D1B019F9F" author="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F." box="[458,804,727,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1267 - 273" refId="ref1781" refString="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F. (2000) Two new Allocapnia from eastern North America (Plecoptera: Capniidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 93, 1267 - 273." type="journal article" year="2000">Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and the small button­like dorsal process of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954674FFD45198E9E76" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2000" box="[264,427,767,792]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sequatchie">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954674FFD45198E9E76" box="[264,427,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sequatchie</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 10–11, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC9546420FD451BF49E77" author="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F." box="[615,977,767,793]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1267 - 273" refId="ref1781" refString="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F. (2000) Two new Allocapnia from eastern North America (Plecoptera: Capniidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 93, 1267 - 273." type="journal article" year="2000">Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner 2000</bibRefCitation>
) contrasts with the bar­like process of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC95467C9FC9D19CF9E2E" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[398,490,807,832]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC95467C9FC9D19CF9E2E" box="[398,490,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC95464FEFC9D1B3C9E2E" baseAuthorityName="Claassen" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[697,793,807,832]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recta">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC95464FEFC9D1B3C9E2E" box="[697,793,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. recta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group are difficult to differentiate (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC954628AFC9D19B89E07" author="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 166" refId="ref1984" refString="Ross, H. H. &amp; Ricker, W. E. (1971) The classification, evolution, and dispersal of the winter stonefly genus Allocapnia. Illinois Biological Monographs, 45, 1 - 166." type="journal article" year="1971">Ross &amp; Ricker 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B07472EC95467EDFCF51B2D9E07" author="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F." box="[426,776,847,873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1267 - 273" refId="ref1781" refString="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; Kirchner, R. F. (2000) Two new Allocapnia from eastern North America (Plecoptera: Capniidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 93, 1267 - 273." type="journal article" year="2000">Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC95465B4FCF51C699E06" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[1011,1100,847,872]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC95465B4FCF51C699E06" box="[1011,1100,847,872]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be reliably distinguished from other members of this group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C367657D472EC954674FFC7D1CB09827" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC236F6472EC954674FFC7D194B9E8E" blockId="2.[264,1324,967,1353]" box="[264,366,967,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954674FFC7D194B9E8E" box="[264,366,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236F6472EC954677FFC551B7999C7" blockId="2.[264,1324,967,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954677FFC5519DC9966" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[312,505,1007,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954677FFC5519DC9966" box="[312,505,1007,1032]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Allocapnia sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54C68854472EC9546560FC551B7C9967" box="[807,857,1007,1033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
locality. Cold Spring emanates from a sandstone capstone layer near the summit of Monte Sano in northern 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC9546273FBAD1C87995F" box="[1076,1186,1047,1073]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Alabama</collectingRegion>
. The spring flows down a boulder­laden, high­gradient channel prior to sinking within fractured limestone. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC95467CAFBDD1A7499EE" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[397,593,1127,1152]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC95467CAFBDD1A7499EE" box="[397,593,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Allocapnia sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be found from similar habitats along the Cumberland Plateau both in 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC95467F8FB351A0C99C7" box="[447,553,1167,1193]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Alabama</collectingRegion>
and north into 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC954649BFB351B7D99C7" box="[732,856,1167,1193]" country="United States of America" name="Tennessee" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Tennessee</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236F6472EC954677FFB0D1CB09827" blockId="2.[264,1324,967,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
The known ranges of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954640AFB0D1AF599BE" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1952" box="[589,720,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loshada">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954640AFB0D1AF599BE" box="[589,720,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. loshada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546553FB0D1B9299BE" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2000" box="[788,951,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sequatchie">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546553FB0D1B9299BE" box="[788,951,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sequatchie</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not overlap with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC9546281FB0D1D0699BE" authorityName="Grubbs" authorityYear="2006" box="[1222,1315,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sano">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC9546281FB0D1D0699BE" box="[1222,1315,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. sano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC954674FFB6519D19996" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1952" box="[264,500,1247,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loshada">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC954674FFB6519D19996" box="[264,500,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Allocapnia loshada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Appalachian species known from a small geographic area encompassing eastern 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC954645FFABD1AB6984F" box="[536,659,1287,1313]" country="United States of America" name="Tennessee" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Tennessee</collectingRegion>
, southwestern 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC954650EFABD1B89984F" box="[841,940,1287,1313]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Virginia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F814472EC95465B5FABD1CBE984F" box="[1010,1179,1287,1313]" country="United States of America" name="West Virginia" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">West Virginia</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D75472EC95462EDFABD19A09826" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Allocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sequatchie">
<emphasis id="B909EAE4472EC95462EDFABD19A09826" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Allocapnia sequatchie</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected only from Tennessee’s Sequatchie River Basin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
